---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Natred's privacy policy explaining how we collect, use, and protect your personal information in accordance with South African POPIA regulations."
>
  <HeroSection
    title="Privacy Policy"
    subtitle="How we protect your information"
    compact={true}
    showCta={false}
  />

  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="policy-content">
        <div class="policy-intro animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>
          <p class="intro-text">Avian Forge (Pty) Ltd, trading as Natred ("we," "us," or "our"), respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information in accordance with the Protection of Personal Information Act 4 of 2013 (POPIA) and other applicable South African laws.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p>We may collect the following types of personal information:</p>

          <h3>1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Contact information (name, email address, phone number, business address)</li>
            <li>Business information (company name, job title, industry)</li>
            <li>Communication records (emails, support tickets, call logs)</li>
            <li>Billing information (invoicing details, payment records)</li>
            <li>Technical information you share for support purposes</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>1.2 Information Collected During Service Delivery</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>System and network logs necessary for IT support</li>
            <li>Configuration data for managed systems</li>
            <li>Technical diagnostic information</li>
            <li>User activity logs where required for troubleshooting</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>1.3 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Website usage data (pages visited, time on site)</li>
            <li>Device and browser information</li>
            <li>IP addresses</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>We use your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Delivery:</strong> To provide IT support, consulting, and other services you've engaged us for.</li>
            <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To respond to inquiries, provide updates, and communicate about our services.</li>
            <li><strong>Billing and Administration:</strong> To invoice for services, process payments, and maintain business records.</li>
            <li><strong>Service Improvement:</strong> To improve our services and develop new offerings.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> To comply with legal obligations and protect our legal rights.</li>
            <li><strong>Security:</strong> To protect our systems, networks, and clients from security threats.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>3. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
          <p>We process your personal information based on one or more of the following grounds:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Where you have given explicit consent for specific processing activities.</li>
            <li><strong>Contract:</strong> Where processing is necessary to perform a contract with you or take steps at your request before entering a contract.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> Where we need to comply with a legal obligation.</li>
            <li><strong>Legitimate Interest:</strong> Where processing is necessary for our legitimate business interests, provided these don't override your rights.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>4. Information Sharing</h2>
          <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Third parties who help us deliver services (e.g., hosting providers, software vendors). These providers are bound by confidentiality agreements.</li>
            <li><strong>Business Partners:</strong> Where we've referred work to technical partners, with your knowledge.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law, court order, or regulatory authority.</li>
            <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with any merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, with appropriate safeguards.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
          <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information, including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Encryption of data in transit and at rest where appropriate</li>
            <li>Access controls limiting who can view personal information</li>
            <li>Regular security assessments and updates</li>
            <li>Staff training on data protection</li>
            <li>Secure disposal of data when no longer needed</li>
          </ul>
          <p>While we take reasonable precautions, no system is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security of your information.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>We retain personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes it was collected, or as required by law. General retention periods:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Client records:</strong> Duration of relationship plus 7 years (legal/tax requirements)</li>
            <li><strong>Communication records:</strong> 3 years from last contact</li>
            <li><strong>Technical logs:</strong> As needed for service delivery, typically 90 days to 1 year</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing contacts:</strong> Until consent is withdrawn</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>7. Your Rights Under POPIA</h2>
          <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request confirmation of what personal information we hold about you and obtain a copy.</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your information where we no longer have a lawful basis to retain it.</li>
            <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to processing based on legitimate interests.</li>
            <li><strong>Withdraw Consent:</strong> Where processing is based on consent, withdraw that consent at any time.</li>
            <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request your information in a machine-readable format where technically feasible.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>To exercise these rights, contact us using the details in Section 10.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>8. Cross-Border Transfers</h2>
          <p>Some of our service providers may be located outside South Africa. Where we transfer personal information internationally, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place, such as:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Transfers to countries with adequate data protection laws</li>
            <li>Contractual protections with the receiving party</li>
            <li>Your consent where appropriate</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>9. Cookies and Website Tracking</h2>
          <p>Our website may use cookies and similar technologies. These help us understand how visitors use our site and improve your experience. You can control cookies through your browser settings.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
          <p>For privacy-related inquiries, to exercise your rights, or to lodge a complaint:</p>
          <div class="contact-info">
            <p><strong>Avian Forge (Pty) Ltd (trading as Natred)</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:service@natred.com">service@natred.com</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>11. Information Regulator</h2>
          <p>If you're not satisfied with our response to a privacy concern, you may lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator:</p>
          <div class="contact-info">
            <p><strong>The Information Regulator (South Africa)</strong></p>
            <p>JD House, 27 Stiemens Street, Braamfontein, Johannesburg, 2001</p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> complaints.IR@justice.gov.za</p>
            <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.justice.gov.za/inforeg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.justice.gov.za/inforeg/</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated to active clients. The "Last updated" date at the top indicates when this policy was last revised.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .policy-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .policy-intro {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
    padding-bottom: 30px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--dark-gray);
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--natred-orange);
    font-size: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .intro-text {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .policy-section {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    padding-bottom: 40px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--dark-gray);
  }

  .policy-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .policy-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .policy-section h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin-top: 25px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .policy-section p {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  .policy-section ul {
    margin-top: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .policy-section li {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    padding-left: 25px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .policy-section li::before {
    content: '\2022';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--natred-orange);
  }

  .policy-section li strong {
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .contact-info {
    background: var(--charcoal);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--natred-orange);
    margin-top: 15px;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .contact-info p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .contact-info a {
    color: var(--natred-orange);
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .contact-info a:hover {
    color: var(--white);
  }
</style>
